{"type":"message","id":"efa4b253","parentId":"00282ea7","timestamp":"2026-04-15T05:40:52.106Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if after installing the agent-browser-cli skill, I would be able to use it. Let me think about this:\n\n1. The skill provides a CLI tool `agent-browser` that's installed globally via npm\n2. The skill's SKILL.md describes how to use the commands\n3. As an AI, I can execute shell commands via the `exec` tool\n4. So yes, I could run `agent-browser` commands via exec\n\nBut wait - the skill itself is just the documentation/SKILL.md. The actual `agent-browser` CLI needs to be installed separately via `npm install -g agent-browser`. \n\nOnce installed, I could invoke it through exec since the skill just provides usage documentation - it doesn't give me new tool capabilities, just instructions on how to use an already-installed tool.\n\nActually, I need to reconsider this. Looking at the skill structure, when I call `exec` with a command, I'm executing it in a Linux environment. But browser automation typically requires a display and user profile - headless mode should work in a server environment, though I'd need to verify that dependencies like Playwright are properly set up.\n\nThe real question is whether `agent-browser` is actually installed on this system. I could check if it's available, but even if it is, running browser automation in a headless Linux environment has limitations - no real display, potential sandbox restrictions, and the browser needs to be configured to run without one. So while I could theoretically use the tool if it's installed, there are environmental constraints that might prevent it from working fully.\n\nI should be straightforward about what I can and can't do: the skill provides the documentation and commands, but I can only use them if the tool is actually installed on the system and the environment supports headless browser operation.","thinkingSignature":"390cecec8019156518fee8575c35bbb6972d91f00e6e6265a15989ad42548f5e"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n装了的话，**我能用**，但有限制：\n\n**我能做的：**\n- 通过 `exec` 调用 `agent-browser` 命令\n- 发送指令让浏览器打开网页、点击、填表、截图、提取数据\n\n**限制：**\n1. **需要 `agent-browser` 本身已安装**（`npm install -g agent-browser`）\n2. **无头模式（headless）** — 服务器/Linux 环境没有图形界面，浏览器在后台跑，没法给你看实时画面（但截图可以证明操作）\n3. **显示服务器** — 如果需要真浏览器画面，需要 X server 或 VNC\n\n**对你来说的实际体验：**\n- 你发指令 → 我执行浏览器操作 → 返回结果给你\n- 你看不到我操作的浏览器窗口，但我会截图给你看结果\n\n---\n\n简单说：**装了我能帮你做浏览器自动化任务，但你在远程看不到浏览器界面，只能看到结果截图或提取的数据。**\n\n要装吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":302,"output":562,"cacheRead":76928,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":77792,"cost":{"input":0.00009059999999999999,"output":0.0006744,"cacheRead":0.00461568,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00538068}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776231639332,"responseId":"062e57d66f6a4a82430f3cef49292feb"}}
