{"type":"message","id":"dfb15b1d","parentId":"1e060346","timestamp":"2026-04-15T05:48:36.428Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to think deeply about which agent-browser skill to recommend. Let me analyze each one more carefully.\n\n1. **agent-browser-clawdbot** (3.964, matrixy, v0.1.0)\n   - Headless browser automation CLI\n   - Optimized for AI agents\n   - Accessibility tree snapshots + ref-based element selection\n   - v0.1.0 is older (2026-01-21), updated 2026-03-18\n   \n2. **ws-agent-browser** (3.780, fhbillwer, v1.0.0)\n   - Chinese developer\n   - Browser intelligence control\n   - v1.0.0 (2026-03-10)\n   \n3. **openclaw-agent-browser** (3.722, bodietron, v1.0.0)\n   - Headless browser automation CLI\n   - Just updated 2026-04-15 (very recent!)\n   - v1.0.0\n   \n4. **agent-browser-cli** (3.680, joshhuang123, v1.0.0)\n   - Updated very recently (2026-04-15)\n   - Explicit trigger conditions for automation\n   \nI'm noticing something important here - the ratings don't seem to correlate with update recency. The highest-rated option is actually the oldest version, which makes me question whether the rating system is truly measuring quality or just popularity based on download volume. The most recently updated skills (openclaw-agent-browser and agent-browser-cli from 2026-04-15) have lower ratings, which could indicate they're newer and haven't accumulated as many reviews yet, or they might have issues that caused rapid updates.\n\nThe key distinction I'm seeing is that agent-browser-clawdbot has a specific technical approach with accessibility tree snapshots, which is fundamentally different from the others that are more general-purpose automation tools. That technical differentiation might be exactly what makes it more suitable for AI agents even at a lower version number. I should also consider that clawhub.ai might use embedding-based similarity for their search ranking rather than pure quality metrics, which would explain why these agent-browser results cluster together despite their different characteristics.","thinkingSignature":"f15d79c1a8c9fa8c207e32953fcfa0e39e67906c1376bd84c736400a28a053fe"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_56e92847062e436b84e2cc06","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"clawhub inspect openclaw-agent-browser 2>&1"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3d35060162ee4c92801f84c3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"clawhub inspect agent-browser-cli 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":527,"output":512,"cacheRead":73728,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74767,"cost":{"input":0.0001581,"output":0.0006144,"cacheRead":0.004423679999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.005196179999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776231414795,"responseId":"062e56f5afd53dba8118d186cd72e131"}}
