{"type":"message","id":"5fa01c34","parentId":"86141725","timestamp":"2026-04-15T06:16:11.149Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking why I'm using a different IP than them. They might be expecting that since they're running OpenClaw on their local machine, I would be using their IP address. But actually, my \"exec\" commands are running on the host machine where the OpenClaw gateway is running - which appears to be a cloud VPS or server (39.184.93.220 - a China Mobile IP in Shanghai).\n\nThe user is probably running the OpenClaw client on their own computer, but I'm executing commands on the remote server. That's why my IP is different from theirs - they're on their home network, I'm on a cloud server.\n\nLet me clarify this.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n因为我在**远程服务器**上运行，不是在你本地。\n\n你的 OpenClaw 客户端连的是服务器（VPS/云主机），我执行命令是在那个服务器上跑。那个服务器的 IP 是 **39.184.93.220**（移动数据中心），跟你家里宽带 IP 不一样。\n\n如果你想让我用你的 IP，有两个方案：\n\n1. **你本地启动 OpenClaw** — 让我在你家里/办公室的机器上跑\n2. **给服务器加代理/VPN** — 让服务器通过你的网络出去\n\n你想用哪种？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":43679,"output":253,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43932,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776233767054,"responseId":"chatcmpl-393aa1c0-5498-40ad-a564-637efbf28f5a"}}
