{"type":"message","id":"a4065e27","parentId":"738c1e49","timestamp":"2026-04-15T06:20:15.051Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is frustrated and says their IP is Zhejiang, not Shanghai. Let me check what's happening - maybe there's confusion or a routing issue. The user is saying their IP should be in Zhejiang province, not Shanghai.\n\nBut my IP shows 39.184.93.220 which is showing Shanghai in ipinfo.io. That's weird if the user is in Zhejiang.\n\nWait - maybe the WSL is using some kind of network translation or VPN? Or maybe there's an issue with how the IP is being detected.\n\nLet me think about the possibilities:\n1. WSL network is NAT'd through the Windows host, but somehow going through a proxy/VPN\n2. There's some network configuration issue\n3. The user is correct and my detection is wrong\n\nActually, wait - the user's network card shows 172.23.111.196 which is an internal IP. The external IP that's showing up (39.184.93.220) might be going through some mobile network connection or a VPN that the user isn't aware of.\n\nOr maybe the WSL is set up to use some proxy server by default in their environment.\n\nLet me just accept whatever the user says and ask them what their actual IP shows as, or suggest they check their network configuration.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"019d8fcc0f1f8f46a1cd194ade1f0fc2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s --max-time 5 ifconfig.me 2>&1; echo \"---\"; curl -s --max-time 5 ip.sb 2>&1"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":1404,"output":310,"cacheRead":43008,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44722,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776233991579,"responseId":"019d8fcbc1014a0feb10870c39a7ec1a"}}
