{"type":"message","id":"56da37a6","parentId":"2ce9f476","timestamp":"2026-04-15T06:27:36.712Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking how I can use their hotspot IP. \n\nThe issue is: I'm running in the WSL on their local machine, but the network goes through their regular broadband, not through their phone hotspot. \n\nFor me to use their hotspot IP, they would need to:\n1. Connect their computer to the phone hotspot (via WiFi or USB tethering)\n2. Then the network traffic would go through the phone's mobile network\n\nIf they connect their laptop to the phone hotspot, then WSL would also use that network (by default, WSL uses the Windows host's network interface). Then my IP would change to the mobile carrier IP from their phone.\n\nBut actually, they might need to disconnect from宽带 and only use hotspot for this to work properly.\n\nLet me explain how this would work.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n你把电脑**连上手机热点**（WiFi 或 USB 共享），WSL 就会跟你手机走同一个网络，IP 就变成移动/电信的了。\n\n操作：\n1. 电脑 WiFi 断掉宽带，连上手机热点\n2. 或者 USB 连手机开 USB 网络共享\n3. 然后我再测\n\n连上告诉我，我来试。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":46668,"output":241,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46909,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776234414592,"responseId":"019d8fd18fef2a128b849c060e73399e"}}
