{"type":"message","id":"6ff0e973","parentId":"86775fb6","timestamp":"2026-04-15T06:32:40.644Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Exit code 7 means \"Failed to connect to host\". The proxy isn't reachable. But wait - this is from the server side. The proxy is on the user's Windows machine, but the OpenClaw is running in WSL, which should have network access to the Windows host via 127.0.0.1.So if the proxy is on Windows at 127.0.0.1:6244, and the WSL can access Windows's localhost, then curl from WSL should be able to reach 127.0.0.1:6244.But it failed. Either:\n1. The proxy isn't actually running on Windows2. WSL can't reach Windows's localhost for some reason (network隔离)\n3. The port is wrong\n\nLet me check if the port is even listening from WSL's perspective.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"019d8fd77984836990c31839dc73697a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"nc -zv 127.0.0.1 6244 2>&1 || timeout 2 bash -c 'cat < /dev/tcp/127.0.0.1/6244' 2>&1"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":451,"output":240,"cacheRead":46592,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47283,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776234729506,"responseId":"019d8fd70b59131cc3eb8203ae9437fe"}}
