{"type":"message","id":"bc14bb72","parentId":"bc79cdf5","timestamp":"2026-04-15T06:57:51.759Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to try connecting to their Edge browser. Let me first check if Edge is available on the Windows side, and then guide them to start Edge with remote debugging port enabled.\n\nThe steps:\n1. First, check if Edge is installed (I already know it is from earlier - /usr/bin/chromium-browser exists but that's Linux. Edge is on Windows)\n2. Ask the user to start Edge with the debugging port\n3. Try to connect from WSL to the Windows Edge via localhost:9222\n\nWait, but there's a network consideration - WSL and Windows share the same localhost, so if the user starts Edge with --remote-debugging-port=9222 on Windows, WSL should be able to reach it at localhost:9222.\n\nLet me first check if there's already an Edge process running with debugging port, and then guide the user.","thinkingSignature":"89d1b1f363501476deac3c0fe90a049586afa11fcab1ebbe6bf260a25722a78d"},{"type":"text","text":"\n第一步：先检查 Edge 调试端口是否已开：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h2sdkjugtr31_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s --max-time 3 http://127.0.0.1:9222/json/version 2>&1 || echo \"9222 not open\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":245,"cacheRead":60950,"cacheWrite":108,"totalTokens":61357,"cost":{"input":0.0000162,"output":0.000294,"cacheRead":0.0036569999999999997,"cacheWrite":0.0000405,"total":0.0040076999999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776236258143,"responseId":"062e69e1e0a3cd1c45f6221672f72635"}}
