{"type":"message","id":"5f3eb15b","parentId":"b0b19c57","timestamp":"2026-04-15T07:02:02.219Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user says Edge has started in debug mode. Now I need to check if the debug port is accessible from WSL. The port 9222 is on Windows localhost, but WSL needs to access it. Since WSL and Windows share localhost, I should be able to access it via 127.0.0.1:9222. But wait - is that actually the case? Let me check if WSL can reach Windows's localhost.\n\nActually, by default, WSL2 can access Windows localhost via the Windows IP. But 127.0.0.1 in WSL is WSL's own localhost, not Windows's. Let me check what the situation is.\n\nIn WSL2, to access Windows localhost from WSL, you typically use the Windows IP (like 172.x.x.x). But there's also a way to enable localhost forwarding.\n\nFor now, let me just try curl to localhost:9222 from WSL and see what happens.","thinkingSignature":"74bd8a608a3a33c4874f78f0f99728a30f0b9d967cfee6059136959fcbbed6f9"},{"type":"text","text":"好！现在检查 WSL 能不能连上这个端口：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1puvp0zn0mgq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s --max-time 5 http://127.0.0.1:9222/json/version 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":261,"cacheRead":61671,"cacheWrite":68,"totalTokens":62054,"cost":{"input":0.0000162,"output":0.00031319999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0037002599999999995,"cacheWrite":0.0000255,"total":0.0040551599999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776236511640,"responseId":"062e6adf865a80862ea1d93194e50b27"}}
