{"type":"message","id":"886ed33e","parentId":"91c23a2f","timestamp":"2026-04-15T07:02:24.982Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Code 28 = connection timeout. Neither 127.0.0.1 nor 172.23.96.1 work for port 9222.\n\nThere might be a firewall issue, or the Windows Defender firewall is blocking incoming connections to port 9222.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. Maybe I need to check if the Edge debug port is actually listening on the right interface. Sometimes the debug port only listens on localhost (127.0.0.1), not all interfaces.\n\nLet me ask the user to check the Edge process and see what ports it's listening on.","thinkingSignature":"8ca33b0fb257fb06f651980050493a70fc885b84bd0c2bf290613b2b4a10ad6a"},{"type":"text","text":"连不上，可能是防火墙或者端口只监听 localhost。让我查一下：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_53obk99sq42h_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"netstat -an 2>/dev/null | grep 9222 || ss -tlnp 2>/dev/null | grep 9222 || echo \"no 9222 found\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42295,"output":197,"cacheRead":20080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62572,"cost":{"input":0.0126885,"output":0.0002364,"cacheRead":0.0012047999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.014129699999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776236537227,"responseId":"062e6af77d2c0d58a826c7f1d0e90404"}}
