{"type":"message","id":"85bd4cd3","parentId":"bd2fdbcc","timestamp":"2026-04-15T07:02:33.594Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The netstat and ss commands aren't finding port 9222. But these are running in WSL, not Windows. So I need to check from Windows side.\n\nWait - but I can also just ask the user to check via command line if the port is listening. Let me also try using PowerShell to check if the Edge is running with the debug port.\n\nActually, maybe I should try a different approach - use Python to try to connect to various possible Windows host IPs, or try to use the Windows IP directly.\n\nBut actually, the simplest issue might be that the Edge debug port isn't actually running on 9222 on the Windows side. Let me ask the user to check via CMD:\n\n```\nnetstat -an | findstr 9222\n```\n\nThis will show if anything is listening on 9222.","thinkingSignature":"954e1085b4851b4b9fac36c0152e944c37aaf4008ad21c905f5c61f21b2cdb8c"},{"type":"text","text":"在 **Windows CMD** 帮我查一下 Edge 调试端口是否真的在跑：\n\n```\nnetstat -an | findstr 9222\n```\n\n把结果发给我。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42513,"output":205,"cacheRead":20080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62798,"cost":{"input":0.012753899999999999,"output":0.00024599999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0012047999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.014204699999999997}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776236545101,"responseId":"062e6aff4619fcffbe4ff9597274378d"}}
