{"type":"message","id":"55fc5db8","parentId":"27310237","timestamp":"2026-04-15T07:03:15.621Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Edge debugging port 9222 is listening only on 127.0.0.1 (localhost), not on all interfaces. That's why WSL can't reach it - WSL sees Windows as a separate machine on the network, and 127.0.0.1 from WSL refers to WSL itself, not Windows.\n\nTo fix this, the user needs to either:\n1. Use `0.0.0.0:9222` instead (but Edge doesn't support this directly)\n2. Use a different approach - maybe port forwarding\n3. Or the user needs to use a different debugging port that listens on all interfaces\n\nHowever, Edge's remote debugging only listens on localhost by default. One trick is to use `edge://inspect` or a different approach.\n \nI could try setting up port forwarding from Windows to route the traffic, or use `netsh interface portproxy` if that's available. But there's another option - if the user has PowerShell remoting or SSH set up between WSL and Windows, that could work too. The simplest solution though is probably just to add a port proxy from Windows to forward the traffic.\n\nActually, I realize the user could also just use `adb reverse` if ADB is available, or even better, they could add a firewall rule to allow inbound connections to port 9222 on the Windows side.\n\nLet me think about the most practical approach: the user enables the rule via netsh, or they could use SSH tunneling. But actually, the simplest solution might be to have them run a Python script on Windows that acts as a simple proxy to relay traffic from an external interface to localhost:9222.\n\nWait, or they could use ngrok or similar tools to tunnel to the port. Actually, netsh portproxy would work well here - I can have them run the command to set up port proxying from an external IP to localhost:9222. Though that requires admin privileges.\n\nAlternatively, if they're on Windows 10/11, they could just modify the Edge shortcut to add `--remote-debugging-port=9222` and `--host-resolver-rules` to bind to all interfaces instead of just localhost.","thinkingSignature":"da201286f69f7e09bdd8de935abc66f08c4eb0691803c489bde688a035e034e3"},{"type":"text","text":"9222 只监听 `127.0.0.1`，WSL 跨不过来。需要加一个端口转发。\n\n在 **Windows CMD（管理员权限）** 运行：\n\n```\nnetsh interface portproxy add v4tov4 listenport=19222 listenaddress=0.0.0.0 connectport=9222 connectaddress=127.0.0.1\n```\n\n然后再告诉我，我连 `http://<你电脑IP>:19222`。\n\n或者你有办法让 Edge 的调试端口监听所有 IP 吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":554,"cacheRead":61787,"cacheWrite":444,"totalTokens":62839,"cost":{"input":0.0000162,"output":0.0006648,"cacheRead":0.00370722,"cacheWrite":0.0001665,"total":0.00455472}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776236577981,"responseId":"062e6b20219c631622032740b614c146"}}
