{"type":"message","id":"464cb24f","parentId":"b4c1fd74","timestamp":"2026-04-15T07:16:29.524Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying they just created a new account (\"新建的账户\"), and is questioning why I'm showing an account called \"明天见\" with 11 years of age. They seem confused or suspicious.\n\nWait - I need to think about this more carefully. When the user ran the Edge debugging command with `--user-data-dir=\"%TEMP%\\edge-debug-profile\"`, it creates a brand new temporary Edge profile. This should have been a fresh browser with no login.\n\nBut I found:\n- Page with URL `https://tieba.baidu.com/home/main?id=tb.1.fb843a56.BUo9zAYTr` - this is \"明天见\" with 11 years\n\n\n- This is very suspicious because the temporary profile should have been empty\n\nThe user claims they just created a new account, but I'm seeing an old account with 11 years of history. Either there's a mismatch between the user accounts on the Windows system, or the temporary profile somehow retained or accessed previous session data. I need to clarify which account they're actually signed in with on their end.\n\nSince they're saying they just created a new account, they should be viewing that new one in the Edge window right now. I should ask them to check what's actually visible in their browser - maybe they're looking at a different page than the one my code is connected to, or the CDP connection is pointing to a different browser context than what they're seeing.","thinkingSignature":"c01c57cbf990a3f62ed77844335a51a8a639b49ee01d90e6133d7ae5ff11581b"},{"type":"text","text":"等等，你说刚建新账户？\n\n但 CDP 连接显示的是 `tb.1.fb843a56.BUo9zAYTr` — 这是**明天见**，11年吧龄。\n\n两个可能：\n\n1. **临时 profile 有残留** — `%TEMP%\\edge-debug-profile` 可能没完全清空\n2. **你的 Windows 系统有多个 Edge 配置** — 调试 Edge 用的不是新 profile\n\n你在**调试 Edge 窗口**（CMD 弹出的那个）里，看到的是哪个账号？\n\n截图发我看看。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":54,"output":402,"cacheRead