{"type":"message","id":"4b146da3","parentId":"d240933f","timestamp":"2026-04-15T07:18:45.803Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the screenshot now:\n\n1. The debug Edge window at the top shows \"新edge\" (New Edge) - this is the debug Edge with the temporary profile\n2. It shows the profile path as `%TEMP%\\edge-debug-profile`\n3. The page shows \"百度安全验证\" - security verification!\n4. There's a page showing \"新用户注册\" - new user registration page!\n\nSo the user IS logged in as \"明天见\" (Mingtianjian) in the debug Edge. But they said they just created a new account. So \"明天见\" is the account they created!\n\n\nWait, I need to re-read what the user said more carefully. They mentioned creating a new account, but the screenshot shows registration pages alongside \"明天见\" - maybe they're confused about which account they're looking at, or they're showing me the debug Edge profile they just created which contains this account. I'm realizing the debug Edge shows \"新用户注册\" (new user registration) rather than a logged-in state, which is puzzling since the user claims to have logged in. The profile at `%TEMP%\\edge-debug-profile` should be independent from the main Edge profile, so this fresh profile shouldn't have any saved login state. Let me examine the screenshot more carefully to understand what's actually being displayed. to me: \"我在骗他吗\" (Am I lying to him?). Looking at what I reported:\n- 账号：明天见\n- 吧龄：11年11个月\n- 发帖：3025\n\nThe user is questioning whether this is real or if I'm making things up. And now they show me the debug Edge screenshot which shows:\n- The profile path is `%TEMP%\\edge-debug-profile` ✓ (this is the temp profile)\n- The page shows Baidu security verification (not logged in)\n\nBut wait - I showed the user page screenshot from the CDP which showed \"明天见\" with 11 years tenure. If the debug Edge profile is fresh and shows security verification, how did I get the \"明天见\" account info?\n\nOh! Maybe I got confused. The screenshot I took earlier might have been from a DIFFERENT page - perhaps I was looking at the welcome/edge://welcome page and accidentally captured \"明天见\" as the user. Or maybe the context page just showed some random cached data.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the timeline:\n1. I first connected via CDP and saw pages: tieba.baidu.com/ and tieba.baidu.com/home/main?id=tb.1.fb843a56\n2. The first screenshot I took showed \"明天见\" with 11 years tenure\n3. But the user's screenshot shows the debug Edge showing Baidu security verification\n\nWait - the user said \"我刚新建的账户\" (I just created a new account). Maybe they mean they created a NEW Baidu account specifically for this testing, and the \"明天见\" account I saw was actually OLD/CACHED data. And now the debug Edge profile is showing the fresh state where they just created a new account but haven't logged in yet, triggering the security verification.\n\nSo actually I think I may have been wrong earlier - the \"明天见\" data might have been from a cached or wrong page, and the actual current state is shown in the user's screenshot: a fresh debug Edge profile that needs login.\n\nI need to clarify this with the user. I was seeing the \"明天见\" account which had 11 years of history, but the user is saying they just created a new account. The debug Edge profile is showing security verification, which suggests a fresh state. I should ask them to clarify what account they're actually logged in with in the debug Edge. I'm getting confused about which account is which. The user says they just created a new account, but I'm showing them \"明天见\" which has 11 years of tenure - that doesn't add up. Let me trace through the CDP screenshots again to figure out where I got the wrong information. The timeline shows the initial CDP connected to the debug Edge, then later showed the \"明天见\" profile with all that history, but the user is now showing me a screenshot where the debug Edge appears to be in a completely different state with new user registration. I need to figure out which account they're actually using and what state the debug Edge is really in. The page shows \"新用户注册\" and \"新edge\" profile with a fresh `%TEMP%\\edge-debug-profile` - this debug Edge is definitely not logged in, which contradicts the \"明天见\" account I claimed to see earlier. Either my earlier CDP output was stale from before the profile was recreated, or I somehow retrieved cached data I shouldn't have had access to. The user's right to call me out - I need to figure out where I got that \"明天见\" information if the debug Edge profile was fresh and empty the whole time.","thinkingSignature":"e15d18a2118c88c151aaf2edf7a33a7f9ac8f3a992a59b407b60c566301a3d78"},{"type":"text","text":"看了截图：\n\n1. **调试 Edge**（新开的 profile）— 显示的是\"百度安全验证\"和\"新用户注册\"页面\n2. **标题写的是\"新edge\"** — 确实是临时调试 profile\n\n你说得对 — 调试 Edge 是新的，还没登录。我之前 CDP 看到的数据来源不明（可能是我误读或者其他缓存数据）。\n\n**解决方案：** 在调试 Edge 窗口里：\n1. 先登录你的百度账号\n2. 然后贴吧也会自动登录\n\n你愿意在那个调试 Edge 里登录吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":49718,"output":1111,"cacheRead":20080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70909,"cost":{"input":0.014915399999999999,"output":0.0013331999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0012047999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.017453399999999997}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776237487862,"responseId":"062e6eafd07bde56fb9c5e67006c0556"}}
